olive oil
1 carrot
1 beetroot
2 clove garlic
1 packet Baby Leaves
1 packet beef strips
1 sachet Classic Roast Seasoning
1 packet couscous
¼ tsp salt
¾ cup boiling water
1 tsp honey
drizzle vinegar (balsamic or white wine)
1 packet Dill & Parsley Mayonnaise
½ packet Cow's Milk Feta

• Preheat oven to 240°C/220°C fan-forced.
• Cut carrot into bite-sized chunks. Cut beetroot into 1cm chunks.
• Place veggies on a lined oven tray. Drizzle with olive oil, season with salt and toss to coat.
• Roast until tender, 20-25 minutes.

• Meanwhile, boil the kettle. Finely chop garlic. Roughly chop baby leaves.
• Discard any liquid from beef strips packaging.
• In a medium bowl, combine beef strips, classic roast seasoning and a drizzle of olive oil.

• Place couscous and the salt in a medium heatproof bowl.
• Add the boiling water (3/4 cup for 2 people / 11/2 cups for 4 people) and stir to combine.
• Immediately cover with a plate and leave for 5 minutes. Fluff up with a fork and set aside.

• In a large frying pan, heat a drizzle of olive oil over medium-high heat.
• Cook baby leaves until wilted, 1-2 minutes.
• Add garlic and cook until fragrant, 1 minute.
• Transfer to bowl with couscous.

• Return frying pan to high heat with a drizzle of olive oil.
• When oil is hot, cook beef strips in batches, tossing, until browned and cooked through, 1-2 minutes.
• Return all beef strips to pan, then remove pan from heat. Add the honey and toss to coat.

TIP: Cooking the meat in batches over high heat helps it stay tender!

• To the bowl with couscous, add roast veggies and a drizzle of vinegar and olive oil. Season with salt and pepper.
• Divide rainbow couscous between bowls. Top with honey beef strips.
• Drizzle over dill & parsley mayonnaise and crumble over cow's milk feta (see ingredients) to serve. Enjoy!